üîπ BASIC LEVEL MCQs (10)
1. SSE-CMM primarily focuses on:
A. Network security tools
B. Security engineering process maturity
C. Incident response automation
D. Compliance penalties

2. SSE-CMM stands for:
A. Secure Software Engineering ‚Äì Capability Model
B. Systems Security Engineering ‚Äì Capability Maturity Model
C. Security Services Evaluation ‚Äì Control Model
D. Software Security Evaluation ‚Äì Maturity Model

3. The main purpose of SSE-CMM is to:
A. Detect cyber-attacks
B. Assess and improve security engineering processes
C. Replace ISO 27001
D. Perform penetration testing

4. SSE-CMM was developed to address gaps in:
A. Financial audits
B. Security engineering practices
C. Network performance
D. Software licensing

5. SSE-CMM is best categorized as a:
A. Legal regulation
B. Process maturity model
C. Security tool
D. Audit checklist

6. SSE-CMM evaluates maturity based on:
A. Hardware used
B. Defined process areas and practices
C. Number of tools
D. Incident count

7. SSE-CMM is MOST useful for:
A. End users
B. Organizations developing secure systems
C. Hackers
D. Marketing teams

8. Using SSE-CMM helps organizations to:
A. Eliminate all risks
B. Improve consistency of security engineering
C. Avoid audits
D. Reduce documentation

9. SSE-CMM maturity levels indicate:
A. System performance
B. Capability of security processes
C. Network throughput
D. Compliance penalties

10. SSE-CMM is typically used during:
A. Only operations
B. System lifecycle and development phases
C. Incident response only
D. Post-breach activities

